snippet.textDisplay: I remember one day I was four wheeling ridding and I saw my favorite butterfly. The kind of butterfly that is my favorite is Monarch butterflies. Well I saw that butterfly and I stopped the four wheeler and hold my hand out. And then that thing literally got on my finger and just stayed there. Like it stayed there for a good 15 minutes. I would even walk around with it too. But I am so happy I did land on me though because I got to see a good close up of the butterfly. But after a while I needed it to get off my hand because I kind of was “captured” by the butterfly so yea. That was a special day though. I never forget that butterfly. We actually have a family of monarch butterflies and we see them a lot when we got swimming in our pool. Like I think there is 4 or something but just a special day😂😊
